On November 2, 2009, the President's Economic Recovery Advisory Board (PERAB) held a meeting with the President to discuss long-term, innovation-based ideas to sustain growth and create future jobs. This meeting was the second full board meeting of the PERAB and was live-streamed on the White House website. Attendees included members of the PERAB, such as Anna Burger, John Doerr, and Timothy Geithner, as well as administration staff like David Axelrod and Rahm Emanuel. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss strategies for economic recovery and job creation.